name: Entity A
description: Designates an agent. Normally the primary one.

name: Entity B
description: Designates an agent. Normally a secondary one.

name: Dot
description: Non-semantic element, just used to split lines.

name: Identity
a1: I am A / This A (more from the perspective of the writer)
a1p: A is this place / A is where I am.
a2: You are A / This A (more from the perspective of the reader)
t1b: A is more me than B
t1t: A is more you than B

name: Good
a1: A is good / A is happy
na1: A is bad / A is unhappy
d1: Something good has happened to A. A’s goodness.  A’s goodness / badness.
t1b: A is better than B
t1bn: A is not better than B
t1t: A is more important than B
t1tn: A is not more important than B
td1: A did something good for B/Improves B
do1: C did a good thing A for B

name: Change
d1: A is caught up in change
t1b: A is more able than B
t1bn: A is no more able than B
t1t: A is different to B
t1tn: A is not different to B
td1: A changes into B / A becomes B
n2: A is able to do B

name: Group
d2: H is a part of a collection
t1b: A is more numerous than B
t1bn: A is not more numerous than B
t1t: A is more unique/singular than B
t1tn: A is not more unique/singular than B

name: Event
description: Denotes a place, event, or context.

name: Need
d2: A has control of their destiny
t1b: A is more necessary than B
t1bn: A is not more necessary than B
t1t: A is more likely than B
t1tn: A is not more likely than B

t1bn: A is not friendlier than B

t1tn: A is not more selfish than B

name: Question
do2: C asks B about A, and D answers

name: Want

t1bn: A is not more desired than B

t1bn: A is not more powerful than B

name: Smell
do1: A gives B C to smell

name: Eat

name: Know

name: Scary

name: Time

t1b: A is older than B
t1bn: A isn’t older than B

ud: A and B happen at the same time.
